attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, too large section header offset jd

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a ransomware sample. The binary contains extensive embedded cryptographic libraries (AES, RSA, ChaCha) used for file encryption. It creates a ransom note named "/!__README__!.txt" which instructs the victim to connect to a Tor-based payment site. The presence of numerous FreeBSD-specific strings suggests it was cross-compiled, a common tactic for ransomware targeting Linux and ESXi systems. Key IOCs include the ransom note content "...Use your unique Company ID: 9Q7MOST8ILWRW9XN38DZSK" and the C2/payment URL "http://ebhmkoohccl45qesdbvrjqtyro2hmhkmh6vkyfyjjzfllm3ix72aqaid[.]onion/support/step.php".
